text.section:
This title does not affect the right of any local jurisdiction of the State:
to regulate the quality and character of work of a person who engages in the business of providing electrical services by establishing a system of licenses, permits, fees, and inspections designed to:
ensure compliance with and implementation of State and local building laws; or
enforce other local laws protecting public health and safety;
to require a person who engages in the business of providing electrical services to submit any plan or specification for approval before the electrical services are provided;
to establish a local board;
except as provided in §§ 6-504 and 6-602 of this title, to require an examination before issuing a license to provide electrical services within the local jurisdiction; or
to collect, from a person who is licensed with a local board, fees for:
an examination for a license to provide electrical services;
issuance and renewal of the license; or
an inspection.
